With a cast that includes Dick Miller, Jackie Joseph, and a very young Jack Nicholson as a scene stealing dental patient, director Roger Corman and screenwriter Charles Griffith give us a comic horror masterpiece for the ages!

programme.desc: Gunnar, a long-lost relative of the Cartwright family, arrives in Ponderosa, where the family takes him in for the night. Unknown to the Cartwrights, however, is Gunnar’s leading of The Comancheros, a dangerous band of criminals. After Little Joe and his girlfriend are kidnapped by The Comancheros, the Cartwrights and Gunnar must work things out.

programme.desc: Holmes investigates the death of Sir Charles Farnsworth, who in his will requested that Holmes investigate his death. Holmes discovers that Sir Charles Farnsworth had no shortage of people who wanted him dead.

programme.title: Lucky Silva

programme.title: Clothing Store
programme.desc: A clerk named Stanley finds himself embroiled in the chaotic ongoings of New York City tourists inside an upscale hotel.

programme.title: Father Delivers the Papers

programme.title: Private Buckaroo
programme.desc: An all-star cast including Donald O'Connor, the Andrews Sisters, and Joe E. Lewis help to tell this tale of bandleader Harry James being drafted into the army! Great musical numbers and hysterical gags highlight this treat from World War II, but the unheralded scene stealer in this film is Shemp Howard, who proves that a single Stooge can be just as funny as three!

programme.title: The Nazis Strike (Why We Fight)
programme.desc: Documentary regarding the official testament from the US Government during World War II underscoring why we must fight the various enemies of the Allies.

programme.title: Parlor Bedroom and Bath (1931)
programme.desc: Buster Keaton stars in this comic romp about a shy fellow who pretends to be a ladies man. Jeffrey Haywood (Reginald Denny) wants to marry Virginia (Sally Eilers), but Virginia won’t get married unless her sister (Dorothy Christy) is married off first. Hence, Jeff enlists the unsuspecting Reginald Irving (Buster, in one of his first talkies) to pretend to be a Casanova! The film, based on a popular Broadway play, and directed by longtime Keaton collaborator Edward Sedgwick (The Cameraman, Spite Marriage), was one of MGM’s most successful comedy titles of 1931 and will still make you laugh today!

programme.title: The Amazing Adventure (1936)
programme.desc: Featuring another charming performance from the irresistible Cary Grant, The Amazing Adventure tells the story of a bored millionaire (Grant) who wagers his doctor that he can support himself at a working class job for a year without touching his inheritance. Lushly shot by renowned Czech cinematographer Otto Heller (Peeping Tom) and adapted from E. Phillips Oppenheimer’s novel by Academy Award nominee John L. Balderston (Gaslight) this classic film has enough comedy, romance and drama for the whole family!

programme.title: My Dear Secretary (1948)
programme.desc: Bestselling novelist Owen Waterbury (Kirk Douglas) hires aspiring writer Stephanie 'Steve' Gaylord (Laraine Day) to be his secretary. She thinks this is a good deal until it becomes apparent that Waterbury is no more interested in blondes than books. Romance blooms, but not in the usual way. Written and directed by Charles Martin, the film features a stellar supporting cast that includes Keenan Wynn, Rudy Valle, and Irene Ryan. Also, look for former model and B-movie starlet Virginia Hewitt as the moronic Felicia Adams, one of the wackiest blondes to ever dream of movie stardom!

programme.title: Nurse Edith Cavell (1939)
programme.desc: Anna Neagel’s first Hollywood performance! Featuring a star-making performance from the then largely unknown actress Anna Neagel, Nurse Edith Cavell is a thrilling and heartbreaking biography of a woman who made an indelible mark on World War I history. Directed by frequent Neagel collaborator Herbert Wilcox, and with a supporting cast composed of Hollywood legends like Oscar Nominee Edna May Oliver (Little Women) and Oscar Winner George Sanders (All About Eve), this film is as memorable and celebrated as the woman whose story it tells.

programme.title: Castle of the Living Dead
programme.desc: A traveling theatre troupe are thrilled with their luck when they are invited to the castle of the mysterious but alluring Count Drago. But a chilling prediction from a strange old woman casts a shadow over the impending visit. Once at the castle, the party find a room full of stuffed birds waiting for them...or at least they seem to be. Count Drago has a terrible secret.

programme.title: Horror Express
programme.desc: Christopher Lee stars as a British anthropologist who must transport a mysterious frozen specimen on the Trans-Siberian Express. When passengers wind up dead, he soon suspects that the properties of this specimen are more powerful than he realized. Also starring Peter Cushing, and Silvia Tortosa. Filmed in Spain. (The film earned director Eugenio Martin a special medal at the Catalonian Film Festival in 1972.)

programme.title: Carol Burnett Show - Season 1 Episode 6
programme.desc: Carol hosts Phyllis Diller and Bobbie Gentry amidst a series of comedic skits.

programme.title: Season 13 Episode 67
programme.desc: Comedian Johnny Carson hosts a variety of celebrities in his iconic late night talk show.

programme.title: The Bird With the Crystal Plumage
programme.desc: An American expat in Rome witnesses an attempted murder at an art gallery. He soon learns that it's connected to an ongoing murder spree in the city, and decides to do his own investigation, despite being personally targeted by the killer.

programme.title: The Cat and the Canary (1927)
programme.desc: Cyrus West's relatives have waited 20 years for a reading of his will, and are shocked to learn that Annabelle West, the only remaining heir with his name, inherits everything unless she's proven to be insane. Before anymore can be read, the lawyer disappears! The Cat and the Canary was based on the popular play of the same name and is considered the starting point of Hollywood's infatuation with "old dark house" mysteries. Laura La Plante plays Annabelle, and as the sinister events unfold, even you will be wondering if she's unstable!

programme.title: Fear in the Night (1947)
programme.desc: I DIDN'T WANT TO DO IT, BUT...MY BRAIN WAS HANDCUFFED! Can a man commit MURDER in a dream?...Here is the spine­tingling, blood­freezing answer...different from any mystery you've ever seen!... Based on a story by Cornell Woolrich, the king of psychological suspense, Fear in the Night tells the tale of a man who dreams he killed someone, then suspects it was real! Paul Kelly, DeForest Kelley, and Ann Doran star in this chiller from award winning director Maxwell Shane (The Glass Wall, The Naked Street). How do you solve a murder, when the only clue is a nightmare?

programme.title: Beyond Alantis
programme.desc: A band of adventurers invade a native island determined to grab a reported fortune in buried treasure. The islanders are just as determined to keep their sacred treasure. Complications ensue.

programme.title: Room (1957)

programme.desc: While visiting a small island in the Mediterranean, a man is surprised when residents recognize him and claim that he is a resident of the island that has returned after many years away - even though he has never been there before.

programme.title: Eye Witness (1959)
programme.desc: Photographed in the act of robbing a restaurant and killing a waitress, an older man with no criminal record is suspected by the witnesses. Mike, however, is suspicious and begins to investigate the case.

programme.title: Bloodline
programme.desc: After shooting Luke Grayson in self-defense, Ben Cartwright must protect himself from Grayson’s son, Todd, who seeks to avenge his father’s death.

programme.title: The Grunion Hunt Mystery
programme.desc: Mickey's plan for a grunion hunt with Pat are foiled by a strange character.

programme.title: The Case of the Impromptu Performance
programme.desc: A condemned man scheduled to hang the next day uses his last request to ask Sherlock Holmes to prove his innocence.

programme.title: Dr. Impossible
programme.desc: Medic follows Dr. Konrad Styner and his team of Surgeons as they tackle medical cases inside Los Angeles.

programme.title: The Morrison Story
programme.desc: New York City police officer Barney Ruditsky faces off against organized crime during the Roaring 20s.

programme.title: Gets a Bachelor Apartment
programme.desc: A clerk named Stanley finds himself embroiled in the chaotic ongoings of New York City tourists inside an upscale hotel.

programme.title: No Partiality
programme.desc: In a move towards equal treatment, both Betty and Kathy get to invite a boy to dinner. Turns out - they want to ask the same boy!

programme.title: Million Dollar Kid (1944)
programme.desc: When the East Side Kids tangle with some West Side Crooks, it's a jillion dollar holler! The gang is befriended by a millionaire after saving him from a mugging, but when they realize the man’s son was one of the criminals, they set out to reform him. Leo Gorcey and Huntz Hall star as Muggs and Glimpy, ganging up on the toughest guys in town! This really is the East Side Kids’ fight of fights!

programme.title: Submarine Alert
programme.desc: Looking to pay for his young ward's operation, a radio engineer falls prey to a Nazi spy ring when he loses his job.

programme.title: Wild Guitar
programme.desc: It's an Elvis movie without Elvis! Cult director Ray Dennis Steckler (The Thrill Killers) made his directorial debut with Wild Guitar, a cheesy, campy, surprisingly entertaining musical drama starring Arch Hall Jr. as Bud Eagle, a naïve singer who gets a shot at the big time. Steckler not only directed this frenzy of musical action, but also appears as a menacing thug working for record company crooks. Co-written and produced by Hall's father, Arch Hall Sr., (who should be known as the godfather of exploitation for films like The Chopper and The Sadist) this one really rocks!

programme.title: At War with the Army (1950)
programme.desc: It's Jerry Lewis and Dean Martin in their first staring vehicle! Lewis plays Alvin Korwin, a bumbler who goes from one disaster to the next, while the suave Sgt. Vic Puccinelli (Martin) tries to keep him out of trouble. Director Hal Walker, who had previously worked with the team of Bob Hope and Bing Crosby, found comedy gold in Martin and Lewis. Songs include 'You And Your Beautiful Eyes', and 'Tonda Wanda Hoy'. For trivia buffs, throughout the film, Lewis gives a Boy Scout salute instead of an Army salute.

programme.title: The Life of Christ - Vol. 1
programme.desc: A television mini-series told the life of Christ in a version of the typical Hollywood serial film.

programme.title: Let's Get Tough (1942)
programme.desc: You may think you’ve seen everything, but you never saw The East Side Kids take on a gang of Japanese spies! Riled by the attack on Pearl Harbor, the boys (Leo Gorcey, Huntz Hall, and the rest) discover a real group of Japanese spies in their neighborhood. Are the East Siders bright enough to expose them? Sure they are! It’s good old American propaganda at its finest!

programme.title: Sherlock Holmes: The Woman In Green (1945)
programme.desc: Sherlock Holmes gets the call when several young women turn up dead in London. The only common clue is that each corpse is missing a finger. Holmes suspects a diabolical plot hatched by his arch enemy Moriarty, but the trail leads him to a society of hypnotists, and a mysterious woman. Is she a temptress of pleasure ­ or mistress of murder? Basil Rathbone and Nigel Bruce reprise their roles as Holmes and Dr. Watson, while Henry Daniell and Hillary Brooke are on hand as Moriarty and the alluring woman of the title!

programme.title: Invaders From Space
programme.desc: The evil salamander men have poisoned Earth with a plague, and it is up to Starman (Ken Utsui) to save mankind. But who are these salamander men, and why do they want to destroy us? It's hard to say, but you'll have fun watching them try.

programme.title: Broadway Jungle
programme.desc: A fledgling Hollywood director, desperate for cash to pay his rent, enlists local gangsters to help him produce his next great film. Murder, mayhem, seduction, and simpering starlets ensue.

programme.title: Carol Burnett Show - Season 1 Episode 3
programme.desc: Carol hosts Jonathan Winters and Eddie Albert along with a variety of skits.

programme.title: Season 18 Episode 195
programme.desc: Comedian Johnny Carson hosts a variety of celebrities in his iconic late night talk show.

programme.title: Curse of Bigfoot (1975)
programme.desc: Beware - not of Bigfoot, but of this movie! A group of high school kids go exploring in a cave and stumble upon a mummy, but when they remove it, the nasty old thing comes to life and starts terrorizing their small California town! If this doesn't look exactly like a 1970s movie, that's because producer/director Dave Flocker shot most of it in 1958 as Teenagers Battle the Thing. Bigfoot enthusiasts might be appalled, but lovers of schlock might find this feature to be just what they need!

programme.title: King of the Zombies
programme.desc: Blood­chilling revelations of the weird cult that practices its black magic in the impenetrable jungles of Central America! Dick Purcell, Joan Woodbury, Mantan Moreland, and Henry Victor star in this comedy chiller from Monogram, directed by Jean Yarbrough ( House of Horrors, The Brute Man). It’s all about a trio of plane crash survivors who take refuge in a mansion, where a sinister doctor is conducting zombie experiments. If you can sit through this spine­tingling carnival of shrieks and howls without getting the thrill of a lifetime...you must belong to the living dead!

programme.title: Creature from the Haunted Sea (1961)
programme.desc: Here’s another Roger Corman classic from the golden age of Drive-In schlock! In this spoof of horror and spy thrillers, American gangster Renzo Capetto (Anthony Carbone) decides to kill members of his bungling crew and blame their deaths on a legendary sea creature. What he doesn’t know is that the creature is actually out there!

programme.title: The Sadist
programme.desc: Written and directed by James Landis, this thriller loosely follows the story of the killing spree of Charles Starkweather (later films Badlands, 1973, and Natural Born Killers, 1994, were also based on Starkweather’s tale). Starring Arch Hall, Jr. The Sadist begins with three high school teachers driving through California. Unfortunately, their car breaks down in an abandoned area, where they experience a run in with a bloodthirsty sadist and his girlfriend. A truly terrifying experience, this film will have you on the edge of your seat from start to finish!

programme.title: Chair (1957)
programme.desc: Here he is: the one, the only… GROUCHO! Legendary comedian, Groucho Marx, hosts this laugh-a-minute quiz show, where three couples face off, answering questions of varying difficulty. This game show is sure to make you laugh as contestants struggle to keep up with Marx’s lightning-quick wit and goofy antics.

programme.title: The Big Break (1953)
programme.desc: Friday leads a team in a raid on the house of a very dangerous armed robber, which results in a bloody shootout.

programme.title: Brainwave (1959)
programme.desc: While aboard a United States ship in Japanese waters during World War II, a hospital corpsman is forced to perform surgery on a critically injured Captain Fielding. A doctor on another ship guides the hospital corpsman through the radio.

programme.title: The Man Below (1959)
programme.desc: Mike believes the man who was recently pushed into a well is the same man he was hired to prove is still alive. To prove that this is the right man, Mike must convince miners that the man is still alive, since no one is willing to risk their life rescuing a corpse.

programme.title: Escape to Ponderosa
programme.desc: Ben helps three deserters, escaped from an Army stockade. Learning what they had to deal with, Ben promises to share the truth with his friend who is in charge of the fort.

programme.title: Jed Pays His Income Tax
programme.desc: Granny chases away an IRS agent.

programme.title: The Other Woman
programme.desc: Mickey showcases some home movies which include one with an incriminating scene of his boss.

programme.title: The Case of the Baker Street Bachelors
programme.desc: A political leader is being blackmailed, and to find the blackmailers, Holmes and Watson join a lonely hearts club. Little did thay know things would go awry as Holmes ending up getting arrested.

programme.title: Break Through the Bars
programme.desc: Medic follows Dr. Konrad Styner and his team of Surgeons as they tackle medical cases inside Los Angeles.

programme.title: The Poison Ivy Story

programme.title: and the Blonde Bandit

programme.title: Close Decision

programme.title: The Brave One

programme.title: Adventures of Gallant Bess (1948)
programme.desc: As cowboy Ted Daniels, Cameron Mitchell (Carousel) shares the screen with a magnificent wild horse named Gallant Bess. Ted tames, trains and keeps Bess for himself, but after Ted is gravely injured in a fixed rodeo, Bess is stolen away from him and forced to join a cruel traveling carnival. This fast-paced western is from director Lew Landers (The Adventures of Rin Tin Tin).

programme.title: Son of Monte Cristo (1940)
programme.desc: Louis Hayward, Joan Bennett and George Sanders headline this Oscar-nominated adventure tale set in the Balkans. Revered director Rowland V. Lee (Son of Frankenstein, Tower of London) keeps the action brisk as the Count of Monte Cristo tries to defeat a bullying dictator, and win a beautiful woman in the process. Also, look for Clayton Moore, TV's Lone Ranger, in one of his earliest roles!

programme.title: Dr. Christian Meets the Women (1940)
programme.desc: In the third installment of the six-part “Dr. Christian” series, Jean Hersholt (Grand Hotel) is featured as the eponymous medical professional. Things get interesting for the good doctor as an enigmatic, and possibly dangerous, “professor” rolls into town, promising instant weight loss to the local women. Follow this tale of Dr. Christian as he matches wits with Professor Kenneth Parker, played by screen veteran Rod La Roque (The Ten Commandments). This drama features fine work from Oscar nominated director William C. McGann and a cast that that includes the great Frank Albertson (Psycho).

programme.title: Mohawk (1956)
programme.desc: Kurt Newman (The Fly, Rocketship X­M) directed this bawdy tale of a love that was louder than war drums! With a cast that includes Scott Brady, Rita Gamm, and Neville Brand, the story takes place on a remote army post where an artist romances a trio of women, just as a vengeful settler turns the army and the local Iroquois tribe against each other. Film buffs might like to know that the cinematography for this feature is by four time Oscar nominee Karl Struss, who won an Academy Award in 1929 for his work on Sunrise.

programme.title: Crimes at the Dark House
programme.desc: A madman kills a man who has just inherited a large estate, then impersonates his victim to gain entrance to the estate so he can murder his enemies.

programme.title: Dementia 13 (1963)
programme.desc: Written and directed by a 24-year-old Francis Ford Coppola, "Dementia 13" centers on the dysfunctional Haloran family, who have converged at Haloran Castle to enact a morbid ritual in remembrance of Lady Haloran's (Ethne Dunn) deceased daughter, Kathleen (Barbara Dowling). Secrets shroud Kathleen's demise, and soon there is a mysterious interloper prowling the grounds with a big axe to grind. Genuinely engaging and well-photographed, "Dementia 13" is a bone-chilling horror classic sure to thrill horror enthusiasts and Coppola fans alike.

Featuring appearances by Bowen Yang, Michaela Jaé Rodriguez, Patton Oswalt, Dwyane Wade, Erica Wheeler, and Elvira, Mistress of the Dark, Cassandra Peterson. And don’t miss the special performances by Chanel and the Circus, Mila Jam, and Alsace Carcione.

programme.title: Davis Mallory | Heavy
programme.desc: The music video for "Heavy" by Davis Mallory featuring Blake Lieder and Daisha McBride. The music video for "Lifeline" by Davis Mallory featuring Allouche. The music video for "Little Victory" by Davis Mallory. A Look behind the scenes at Miami Pride 2021 with Davis Mallory

programme.title: Magic H8 Ball
programme.desc: Burned by a cheating boyfriend (and some mild chlamydia), a heartbroken pushover turns to a mysterious Magic 8 Ball for the answers. But as he starts giving into his impulses, he risks his hurt turning into hate-and losing all control.

programme.title: Scales
programme.desc: S1 E1/2/3 | Meet Remy, Gavin, and David living in Atlanta finding balance in their lives. Remy has been single for quite some time, but an unexpected run in, could potentially change his fate./Remy is going to everyone for advice, including 17-year old Dakota Keller. Meanwhile, problems are brewing at home for Gavin and Sheila and David gets a rude awakening from a stranger./A revolving door can allow you to come in and out. In this case, Remy's house happens to be the revolving door, but someone ends up getting stuck. Remy and Sean must deal with their past. Sheila takes control of a situation and confronts Remy. Kevin’s sister, Gloria arrives with an update on Kevin’s progress.

programme.title: Scales
programme.desc: S1 E4/5/6 | Remy struggles to deal with the aftermath of his actions. Gavin and Sheila’s relationship continues to suffer. Meanwhile, David and Caleb find common ground with each other./Kevin returns home and Gloria expresses her doubts. Meanwhile, Dakota has news to share. David’s sister, Jade gives him encouragement to move forward. David reaches out to Caleb. Remy must face his past, for once and for all./In the season finale it’s a night of big reveals as the trio head to Caleb’s game night event. Ron has a question for Remy. It’s a game of all truths and not everyone will come out a winner.

programme.title: Gay Mean Girls
programme.desc: S1 E1-2 | Lucy is a “very good ally” who stares at her best friend Miranda…. a lot. They hatch a plan to start Gay Prom Royalty together to promote equality at their school. Miranda pays Lucy a visit on a day off from school. We get a glimpse into Lucy’s home life.

programme.title: The Millennial Experience
programme.desc: The Millennial Experience is one part dance-for-film and one part documentary. The film explores cultural appropriation vs appreciation, LGBTQIA+ culture, feminism and how these topics impact the Millennial generation. The dance sequences in the film are adapted from director Alex Crozier's stage production MILLENNIALS which focuses on the aforementioned themes. Fourteen on-camera interviews that expound on the main topics were conducted with people of various ages, ethnicities, sexual orientations, and genders . The Millennial Experience seeks to uplift the voices of women, LGBTQIA+, and BIPOC communities in an effort to create a more equitable and just world.

programme.title: Gina Yashere: Laughing To America
programme.desc: Filmed live in San Francisco, CA, UK's premier black female comedian, Gina Yashere, has come to America! Her unique take on being a cultural insider and outsider never fails to raise the roof as she gives us her take on the news gripping the nation.

programme.title: Becoming Queen
programme.desc: There has never been a band like Queen, and there never will again. Take a twenty year ride with the people who knew them best.

programme.title: Love V Kentucky
programme.desc: An intimate account of how two Kentucky attorneys with no background in civil rights navigate their passionate opponents, wrangle their reluctant allies, and convince the U.S. Supreme Court to rewrite our nation’s definition of marriage.

programme.title: Jonathan's Kitchen
programme.desc: S1 E6 | Marianne Tshihamba joins me to create a vegan take on one of my favorite side dishes.

programme.title: Jonathan's Kitchen
programme.desc: S1 E7 | Danny Kaylor-Hawkins joins me to prepare a quiet dinner for our husbands.

programme.title: Coming of Age in Cherry Grove
programme.desc: Founded in 1869, Cherry Grove (Fire Island, NY) is considered by most to be the first openly LGBTQ community in the United States. It has become known as one of the most accepting resort communities in the world – a place where you can not only discover who you are, but also freely experiment with who or what (gender) you may want to become. Cherry Grove is also known for the famous “INVASION” – an annual ritual that takes place every July 4th as a celebration of gender acceptance. This film tells the stories of a variety of long-term residents and what they find so wonderful about life in Cherry Grove.

programme.title: Were You Gay In High School?
programme.desc: Two queer women recall their awkward, closeted high school days of kissing boys and straight-girl crushes.

programme.title: The Q Agenda
programme.desc: S2 E5 | We're joined by Eric and Jose of the Homo Homies Podcast, founder of Marianella luxury soaps David Foote, and we discuss depression amongst LGBTQ youth.

programme.title: The Q Agenda
programme.desc: S2 E6 | We're joined by LGBTQ activist Queen Victoria Ortega, music sensation Georgel, and we find out if adopting a pet can help strengthen relationships.

programme.title: Little Miss Westie
programme.desc: If Ren could go back in time before she was four, she would tell her parents that she wasn’t happy living as a boy. Now, Ren is about to take part in a rite of passage for their community in West Haven, CT as the first out transgirl to compete in the Little Miss Westie Pageant. Coaching her through the competition: Her older brother Luca, who previously took part in the pageant when he lived as a girl. Gender dynamics evolve in front of the viewer’s eyes while two transgender siblings explore who they are in this intimate portrait.

programme.desc: S1 | A Revry Original Reality Series, ‘Putting On’ follows a young entrepreneur, On Mekahel, as he struggles to launch his underwear line with his ex-boyfriend.

programme.title: The Billionaire
programme.desc: A gender-swapped independent film adaptation of George Bernard Shaw's classic play 'The Millionairess', transposed into a contemporary context of Gay Marriage and Asexuality, THE BILLIONAIRE follows a haughty and prudish young billionaire's quest for love, despite all the odds. The film is a throwback to Classic Hollywood films, stylistically and tonally.

programme.title: No Gender! The Queer Life Of An Intersex Manga Artist
programme.desc: Up until age 30, Sho Arai lived as a woman, but was found to be intersex after chromosome testing.

programme.title: Carmín Tropical
programme.desc: Mabel, a muxe, returns home to her village in Oaxaca, Mexico to find her friend's killer.

programme.title: Culture Q
programme.desc: Culture Q is the world’s first weekly queer-centric news series brought to you by the leading global queer streaming network, Revry. This innovative, weekly news series creatively features entertainment, pop culture, lifestyle and political news with wit and insightfully nuanced perspectives. Emphasizing the queer millieu, Culture Q stands to be the leading, weekly forum for boundary-pushing discussions and commentary. Hosted by digital news influencer pioneers, Shira Lazar and Andy Lalwani of the highly successful What’s Trending, Culture Q will feature an ever-changing cavalcade of guests who help capture that X-factor which defines queer culture.

programme.title: Out On Stage
programme.desc: Out On Stage is THE absolutely hilarious and one-of-a-kind, originally produced comedy hosted by Zach Noe Towers! See OUT Magazine's "1 of the 10 comedians to watch in 2018," the comedian that Sarah Silverman calls, "So, SO, SO Funny" and 17 other top-rated Gay and Lesbian stand-up comedians discuss taboo subjects as only they can!

programme.title: The Drag Roast Of Heklina
programme.desc: S1 E1 | Check your political correctness at the door and bring your finest, biggest wig for a raucous, no-holds-barred roast of one of San Francisco’s favorite larger-than-life drag personalities, the one and only Heklina—aka Stefan Grygelko. This Revry Original special features such roasters as Jackie Beat, Julie Brown (Clueless), Peaches Christ, Sister Roma, Alaska Thunderf*ck, and Jinkx Monsoon.

programme.title: Barbelle
programme.desc: S1 E7-10 | Alice and Veronica head to the studio to work on the new album. After Karen informs Alice that Lulu will no longer be working on the new album, Alice realizes this might be the end of her and Lulu's relationship. Veronica attempts to win back Alice by writing the perfect song. Her writer's block leads to a downward spiral of shoplifting and booze only hours before she is set to accompany Brooklyn to prom. Alice confronts Veronica about her poor choices. Veronica wakes up to find The Ghost of Girlfriend's Past waiting to take her on a Dickensian journey through her past. Alice accompanies Brooklyn to her prom in Veronica's stead. Lulu shows up to the prom unannounced, as does another surprise guest.↵

programme.title: Imagraphy: Photography Documentary
programme.desc: Step inside the minds of 16 international masters of photography. They share stories behind their most iconic images and techniques whilst learning their impressions of our world as seen through their lenses.

programme.title: The Maid
programme.desc: When her mistress brings on another servant to help with the chores, a bitter and introverted maid wreaks havoc on the household.

programme.title: CONTRACORRIENTE
programme.desc: Miguel is a fisherman in a tiny Peruvian village where traditions run deep. He is married to the lovely Mariela and about to be a father, but has a secret love affair with Santiago, a painter, who is ostracized by the town because he's gay. After a tragic accident occurs, Miguel must choose between sentencing Santiago to eternal torment or doing right by him and, in turn, revealing their relationship to Mariela and the entire village.

programme.title: DIA NARANJA
programme.desc: Three Latin American women from different backgrounds see their fantasies about the future give way to anxiety as they are hit with the same shocking news: they are pregnant. A colorful, vivacious look at the excitement and drama that often accompanies the prospect of motherhood.

programme.title: CAMINO DEL VINO
programme.desc: Tragedy befalls a world-famous sommelier attending an important wine event when he suddenly, inexplicably loses his palate. His mission to recover his talent leads him on a journey through peerless wineries and beautiful vineyards, but most importantly into his own soul.

programme.title: CAPTAIN ORELLANA
programme.desc: Captain Orellana, a private investigator and former cop specializing in the most impossible mysteries, is tapped for the wackiest, most dangerous case of his long career. With a comical 007-like swagger, Orellna gets to the bottom of the uncanny occurrences in a remote village that seems to be ? POSSESSED!

programme.title: OMNIVORES
programme.desc: A prestigious journalist accepts an undercover writing assignment addressing the recent emergence of "clandestine restaurants," one of which holds secret gatherings where diners feast on human flesh in exchange for large sums of money. What started as a simple job may just end in a bloody nightmare.

programme.title: RABBIT WOMAN
programme.desc: A China-born state employee discovers corruption within the Argentinian police force and bravely sets out to bring an end to its corrupt ties to the Chinese mafia. programme.desc: What does it mean to consume cannabis consciously? - Cleanliness: Look for ethically produced cannabis grown with organic, regenerative methods. Composition of the cannabis plant itself is important. Go beyond Indica and Sativa. Get to know cannabinoid and terpene profiles and their benefits for you. Consider set and setting? Where are you? What are you doing? Who are you with? What’s the purpose of your consumption? Cannaisseurship: Appreciate all that went into this medicine, its taste, smell, feel and how it enhances your everyday life. Creation, inspiration, relaxation, reflection. What does the heightened You want to make of this experience? Enjoy the elevated experience that is Swami Select.

programme.title: Meet Emerald Cup Founder Tim Blake Pt.1

Now in its 15th year, the Emerald Cup is the world's longest running cannabis competition and the only cup focusing on California's heritage sun-grown farms. As a group, The Emerald Cup prides itself in bringing together experts and educators in the cannabis field to our fellow farmers, patients, and patrons each year. It is a community celebration that has grown to become a global movement honoring the year’s finest, organic, sun-grown, cannabis harvest.

programme.desc: This is not machine or commercial cannabis trimming. programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is activist and the former chair of the Women’s March Tamika Mallory. Currently she is the co-founder of the social justice organization Until Freedom. DL, Jasmine, and Tamika share a deep discussion of the after effects of George Floyd’s murder by police, protests, and where civil unrest is headed in America.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest DJ Doug E. Fresh

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Dondre Whitfield
programme.desc: DL’s featured guest on DL Uncut is actor and author Dondre Whitfield. Dondre Whitfield began his career in a recurring role on the NBC sitcom “The Cosby Show”. He’s appeared in soap operas, winning three Daytime Emmy Awards for Outstanding Younger Actor. He’s been in numerous sitcoms and films. Whitfield currently stars in the show Queen Sugar.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Actor Miguel A. Nunez
programme.desc: DL’s featured guest on DL Uncut is actor Miguel Nunez. From TV to film, actor Miguel Nunez spends some time with DL and Jasmine to talk about his career, life as a black actor and discuss some of the issues of today.

programme.title: Ali in the Valley | Easy French Onion Soup
programme.desc: This Easy French Onion Soup is rich, comforting and so good with toasted cheesy bread for dipping! What better way to kick off Season 4 of Ali in the Valley than with a delicious decadent classic French Onion Soup. French Onion Soup is such a classic and SO easy to make! Onions are slowly caramelized until soft and sweet, simmered with beef broth, and just a touch of sugar. It’s topped with crispy croutons, loads of shredded gruyere cheese, and broiled into crispy, cheesy oblivion. So good!

programme.title: Stepdads The Sketch- Ep 1
programme.desc: When infidelity claims the life of Joanne Bates, her children Lisa and Stevie are left in the custody of her fiancé Mike and his brother Jerry. Mike, a straight-laced, hardworking accountant; and Jerry, a wild, unstable, womanizer were both former foster children and together they provide a unique balance of parenting skills for young Lisa and Stevie. - Step Dads starring Ben Sloane (R.I.P.D, Alpha House), Morocco Omari (Empire, 21 Bridges, Homeland, Chicago Fire), Jorie Binion (Chicago P.D) Charles Dunlap (Chicago Fire, Empire), and Jay Davis (Not Another Black Movie, Choke On That: The Series, Not Another Zombie Movie) is a comedy about two polar opposite foster brothers raising two children using non-traditional parenting methods while shedding a satirical light on the importance of adoption. We poke fun at some of the mishaps which comes along with the shock of being a new parent, but ultimately, we hope to spread awareness on adoption, the importance of having fathers and father-figures in the lives of young people, and having a familial loving environment. The moral of our story is that “No family is perfect, but every child deserves to be loved unconditionally, and raised in a reliable, stable support system.”

programme.title: Europa
programme.desc: Discovering and exploring Jupiter's most promising moon, Europa. Europa was named after a Phoenician noblewoman who was abducted by Zeus after he had transformed himself into a bull. Rather fittingly, Zeus established Europa on the island of Crete as its queen, where he had several children with her, including Minos, the legendary king of Crete. In later ages, the continent of Europe would be named after Europa.

programme.title: Space Channel Exclusive- I4's Dr. Sian Proctor
programme.desc: Dr. Proctor is a geoscientist, explorer, space artist, and astronaut. She is the mission pilot for the Inspiration4 all-civilian orbital mission to space. She is also one of The Explorer’s Club 50: Fifty People Changing the World. Her motto is called Space2inspire where she encourages people to use their unique, one-of-a-kind strengths, and passion to inspire those within their reach and beyond. She believes that we need to actively strive for a J.E.D.I. space: a just, equitable, diverse, and inclusive space as we advance human spaceflight.

programme.desc: The second launch attempt of a SpaceX Dragon spacecraft to the International Space Station from Launch Complex 39A at Kennedy Space Center in Florida. Also, launch of Blue Origin's NS17, with its own cargo of NASA research and well as international artwork!

programme.desc: Jupiter is the fifth planet from our Sun and is, by far, the largest planet in the solar system – more than twice as massive as all the other planets combined. Jupiter’s stripes and swirls are actually cold, windy clouds of ammonia and water, floating in an atmosphere of hydrogen and helium. Jupiter’s iconic Great Red Spot is a giant storm bigger than Earth that has raged for hundreds of years.

programme.title: Eating on the Edge of Nowhere
programme.desc: Cambodia and Japan: Taking his obsession with the film Apocalypse Now a little too seriously, Tony sets out for Pailin, reputed to be one of the most dangerous towns on earth. After his journey, Tony returns to Japan.

programme.title: Eating on the Mekong
programme.desc: Mekong River, Vietnam: On the river, Tony drinks a lot of Mekong moonshine with the welcoming owners of a duck farm. Although seduced by his Vietnam experience, Tony is not sure the royal dish Birds Nest Soup is all its cracked up to be.

programme.title: San Sebastian: A Food Lover's Town
programme.desc: San Sebastian, Spain: Tony explores the food-crazed Basque culture. Tony's guide, Chef Luis Irizar, takes Tony into the underworld of Basque gastronomic societies. Later, Tony explores the city's tapas bars.

programme.title: Childhood Flavors
programme.desc: Arcachon, France: Here, Bourdain first learned to love food as a child. Returning for a trip down memory lane, Tony enjoys childhood staples, including steak frites, gaufres (waffles), soupe de pecheur (fisherman's soup) and fresh oysters.

programme.title: Italy: Part 2
programme.desc: The brilliance and grandeur of Italy is demonstrated in five captivating settings. Feel like a tall wildflower in the sun and breeze as the hills of Altomonte billow off into the distance, sooth every aching nerve as you absorb the perfect view along the Tiber River, and more.

programme.title: Shedd Aquarium: Wild Reef
programme.desc: Experience the wonder of the Shedd Aquarium’s wild reef as light dances off the colorful aquatic sea life that peacefully swim past in the crystal-clear water. Ambient sound makes you feel as if you are deep beneath the ocean.

programme.title: South Africa
programme.desc: Rudy Maxa knows that an adventurous safari is a wonderful way to experience South Africa. Get up-close-and-personal with lions, giraffes, elephants, and dozens of other animals in their natural habitat, thanks to robust preservation laws in place.

programme.title: Edinburgh and the Scottish Highlands
programme.desc: Climb the ramparts of Edinburgh Castle. Tee up at the world's most famous golf course, St. Andrews. Tour Deward's whiskey distillery. Stroll Stirling's historic battlefields of Braveheart fame. And, sail the bonny banks of legendary Loch Lomond.

programme.title: London
programme.desc: Rudy answers London's call with an expert tour of its traditional sights and contemporary, cutting-edge attractions. In London's breathtaking countryside you will find mythic castles, the real Alice in Wonderland's candy store, Jane Austen's house, and the mysterious megaliths of Stonehenge.

programme.title: Uzbekistan
programme.desc: In one of his series' most colorful episodes, Maxa takes viewers along the Silk Road in a country that is an emerging economy in Central Asia, Uzbekistan. Marvel at eye-popping mosques built centuries ago, and Rudy joins a family for the preparation of the national dish of "plov."

programme.title: Cape Town
programme.desc: Cape Town is a nexus of cultures in a setting so stunning it is called “Africa's Riviera." Where else in the world can you wake up in a cosmopolitan city, spend the afternoon with penguins, ride a funicular to the edge of the continent, and watch the sun set from a beach with a glass of wine?

programme.title: Garden Route
programme.desc: The Garden Route takes you along a rugged, gorgeous South African coastline. Surfers brave enormous waves and exotic birds watch visitors climb serpentine paths that rise above the coast amid seaside resort towns. Also, visit South Africa's lush wine country in the village of Franschhoek.

programme.title: From Ithaca to the Amazon
programme.desc: Our natural environments are intrinsically more valuable than any grand visions of wealth created using methods detrimental to the Earth. Meet people in New York, India, Russia, Peru, Sumatra, and South Africa who favor health over profit.

programme.title: From Liberia to Mongolia
programme.desc: What we take from and put back into the Earth reflects the very nature of who we are as human beings. Meet people from Washington, Liberia, Macedonia, the Cook Islands, Mongolia, and Chile who believe end results depend upon how we begin.

programme.title: Germany's Via Julia
programme.desc: Discover the ancient Roman military road Via Julia that made rapid travel from Lutetia (now Paris) to Constantinople (now Istanbul) possible. Meet the people who keep the memories of this ancient route intact, and who do their utmost to keep the sacred traditions of their ancestors alive.

programme.title: The Road of Livingstone
programme.desc: “The Road of Livingstone” is a long journey in the footsteps of the British explorer David Livingstone along the Zambezi River, from its mouth in Mozambique all the way to Victoria Falls, at the border of Zambia and Zimbabwe.

programme.title: Eating on the Mekong
programme.desc: Mekong River, Vietnam: On the river, Tony drinks a lot of Mekong moonshine with the welcoming owners of a duck farm. Although seduced by his Vietnam experience, Tony is not sure the royal dish Birds Nest Soup is all its cracked up to be.

programme.title: A Desert Feast
programme.desc: Morocco (Sahara): Tony traverses the Moroccan desert with one goal in mind, to eat a mud-oven-roasted sheep.

programme.title: S7E7 - Paris: Embracing Life and Art
programme.desc: We'll ride a unicorn into the Middle Ages at Paris’ Cluny Museum, get a heavenly look at stained glass in Sainte-Chapelle, go on a tombstone pilgrimage at Pere Lachaise Cemetery, and savor the Parisian cafe scene.

programme.title: S8E7 - Italy's Riviera: Cinque Terre
programme.desc: We'll visit Italy's five tiny seaside towns known as the Cinque Terre, while stopping to fish for anchovies, sip wine from barrels, and savor twinkling Mediterranean vistas.

programme.title: Undiscovered
programme.desc: In Disneyland, walk in Walt Disney’s footsteps and discover the secret spots he created. Step inside the newly constructed Disneyland Dream Suite – a magical space in the park’s New Orleans Square. Just around the corner is another secret spot that very few people even have access to – Club 33.

programme.title: Nature's Erector Set
programme.desc: Central America is home to some of the most breathtaking animals in the world. In vast and dramatic forests, several dynamic species of animal cohabitate - from the fierce jaguar to the clever monkey.

programme.title: New Releases
programme.desc: Check out some of our new content!

programme.title: S8E11 - Prague
programme.desc: We'll visit beautifully preserved Prague to experience its massive castle, evocative Jewish Quarter, thrilling history, infectious music...and perhaps the best beer in Europe.

programme.title: Melbourne Victoria
programme.desc: Jason catches his own lunch at Buxton trout farm, visits a stone fruit orchard, learns how to make sausages at The Green Olive, and learns secrets of cooking from top Australian chef, Guy Grossi.

programme.title: Stuffed like a Pig
programme.desc: Portugal & Southwest France: Visiting his boss's family farm, Tony helps slaughter and feast on a pig the family has been fattening all year. Then, Tony heads to France to experience the rich delights of a foie gras farm.

programme.title: Las Vegas
programme.desc: Explore Las Vegas’ lesser known past. We visit the National Atomic Testing museum to learn about how the desert outside of Vegas was used for testing America’s secret nuclear weapons. We also visit the Mormon Fort, the first permanent non-native settlement in the area, as well as the Neon Museum.

programme.title: S7E2 - Rome: Baroque Brilliance
programme.desc: As we ramble through the heart of Rome, we’ll admire breathtaking Bernini statues and ponder sunbeams inside St. Peter’s Basilica. After dinner, we’ll take a nighttime stroll, lacing together the city’s piazzas and fountains.

programme.title: Running of the Bulls
programme.desc: The Festival of San Fermin in Pamplona, Spain is a deeply rooted celebration of traditional and folkloric events, including the Running of the Bulls. Experience the incredible energy each morning for eight consecutive days as thousands of people run ahead of six, 2,000-pound charging bulls.

programme.title: Wild Delicacies
programme.desc: Cambodia: With a friend along for the ride, Tony travels to Phnom Penh, Cambodia, where he explores a food culture that is both pleasing to the palette and slightly frightening.

programme.title: Eating on the Edge of Nowhere
programme.desc: Cambodia and Japan: Taking his obsession with the film Apocalypse Now a little too seriously, Tony sets out for Pailin, reputed to be one of the most dangerous towns on earth. After his journey, Tony returns to Japan.

programme.title: France's Burgundy and Loire Regions
programme.desc: The Burgundy region boasts top French wines, romantic canals, Romanesque churches, and world-renowned French cuisine. We base in the small town of Beaune and learn about its history of exceptional winemaking. Add a wondrous hot-air balloon ride over the verdant Loire Valley to the itinerary.

programme.title: Berlin
programme.desc: With world-class cultural sites, dynamic new architecture and unstoppable energy, Berlin is a city on the move. We visit the museums - the ancient treasures of the Pergamon and the Egyptian museum, German Expressionism at the Neue Nationalgalerie and the newly designed Jewish Museum.

programme.title: S7E8 - London: Historic and Dynamic
programme.desc: In London, we’ll ponder royal tombs in Westminster Abbey, discover treasures in the British Library, enjoy the vibrant evening scene in Soho, uncover Churchill’s secret WWII headquarters, and straddle the Prime Meridian at Greenwich.

programme.title: Eating on the Mekong
programme.desc: Mekong River, Vietnam: On the river, Tony drinks a lot of Mekong moonshine with the welcoming owners of a duck farm. Although seduced by his Vietnam experience, Tony is not sure the royal dish Birds Nest Soup is all its cracked up to be.

programme.desc: Cambodia: With a friend along for the ride, Tony travels to Phnom Penh, Cambodia, where he explores a food culture that is both pleasing to the palette and slightly frightening.

programme.desc: Cambodia and Japan: Taking his obsession with the film Apocalypse Now a little too seriously, Tony sets out for Pailin, reputed to be one of the most dangerous towns on earth. After his journey, Tony returns to Japan.

programme.title: Cod Crazy
programme.desc: Portugal: Portuguese cuisine holds a dear place in Tony's culinary heart. Tony travels to Porto, home of the famous Port wine, where he is immediately exposed to the codfish and the almost mythical place it holds in Portuguese cuisine and culture.

programme.title: San Sebastian: A Food Lover's Town
programme.desc: San Sebastian, Spain: Tony explores the food-crazed Basque culture. Tony's guide, Chef Luis Irizar, takes Tony into the underworld of Basque gastronomic societies. Later, Tony explores the city's tapas bars.

programme.title: Childhood Flavors

programme.title: Stuffed like a Pig
programme.desc: Portugal & Southwest France: Visiting his boss's family farm, Tony helps slaughter and feast on a pig the family has been fattening all year. Then, Tony heads to France to experience the rich delights of a foie gras farm.

programme.title: Italy: Part 1
programme.desc: Experience the arresting appeal and elegance of Italy in six select locations. Take an invigorating stroll along the Mediterranean coast in Castello Federiciano, marvel at Alberobello’s august trullo dry stone huts, and more.

programme.title: Shedd Aquarium: Underwater Beauty
programme.desc: Fish of all stripes and fluorescence call the crystal-clear waters of Chicago’s Shedd Aquarium home. Water and light collaborate to reveal the tranquil beauty that is life underwater.

programme.title: Tahiti and Bora Bora
programme.desc: For sheer tropical splendor, the islands of Tahiti and Bora Bora stand alone. Hyper blue lagoons, white-sand beaches, fish of every shape, size, and color, as well as a generous and welcoming people make these islands key destinations for travelers from around the world.

programme.title: Polynesia
programme.desc: Experience Polynesia’s rich sea life, crystal blue waters, and vibrant cultures. Tour the diverse reefs of the coral, sea turtle rehabilitation centers, and the many islands and atolls. Participate in the oyster-cultivation process at the major pearl farm, and tour dramatic Marquesas Islands.

programme.title: Montreal
programme.desc: Two of the most unique cities in the world are just north of New England. Here you will find brie, pate, jewel box-patisseries, and “s’il vous plait” right along with bagels, maple syrup, hockey, delis, and bocce ball. Those who forged Montreal and Quebec City braved much to see them flourish.

programme.title: Nova Scotia & Newfoundland
programme.desc: From the charming fishing towns of Nova Scotia to the vast wilderness of Newfoundland, explore the last great open spaces of Eastern North America. A touch of New England, a dash of Germany, here a British fort, there an Irish brogue, the area was peopled by the descendants of hardy colonists.

programme.title: Food, Drink, & Culture
programme.desc: In Istanbul’s Spice Market, brown-gold paprika is carefully molded into pyramids. Cinnamon, cumin, ginger, and cardamom infuse the air. From haggis in Scotland to soba and tea in Japan, from asada in Argentina to bibimbap in Korea, food and drink help illustrate the culture and people of a location.

programme.title: Asian Cities
programme.desc: From the world’s largest city, Tokyo, to the colorful chaos of Delhi, and from the modern miracle of Seoul to the teeming streets of Bangkok, this is your passport to the high-tech marvels and back-street secrets of four of the world’s most amazing cities Asian Cities.

programme.title: From Myanmar to Scotland
programme.desc: Biodiversity is a central component to the successful operation of Earth’s natural systems. Meet people from Haiti, Myanmar, Honduras, Kenya, Canada, and Scotland who spend time and energy securing healthy local environmental regulations.

programme.title: Unfair Game
programme.desc: Zambia and Eswatini (formerly Swaziland) represent two divergent strategies on environmentalism. Meet people from both countries and learn of the successes, failures, and sacrifices they experienced seeking environmental justice.

programme.title: Italy's Via Cassia
programme.desc: Italy’s Via Cassia once led north from Rome to Florence, finally joining the Via Aurelia at Luna (now Luni). As you meander northward along the ancient route, each unique location you visit, and the interesting people you meet there, speak vividly to the region’s steeped history and culture.

programme.title: Cuba
programme.desc: Cuba is a Caribbean Hotspot. The island is a combination of gorgeous landscapes and a unique way of life. Travel from the Guanahacabibes Peninsula to Guantanamo. In Havana, meet students that wonder about their future prospects: exile or revolution?

programme.title: Wild Delicacies
programme.desc: Cambodia: With a friend along for the ride, Tony travels to Phnom Penh, Cambodia, where he explores a food culture that is both pleasing to the palette and slightly frightening.

programme.title: Traditional Tastes
programme.desc: Morocco (Cities): Tony is invited to experience the culinary heart and distinct walled medinas (districts) of the Moroccan city Fes.

programme.title: S7E8 - London: Historic and Dynamic
programme.desc: In London, we’ll ponder royal tombs in Westminster Abbey, discover treasures in the British Library, enjoy the vibrant evening scene in Soho, uncover Churchill’s secret WWII headquarters, and straddle the Prime Meridian at Greenwich.

programme.title: S8E8 - Italy's Verona, Padova, and Ravenna
programme.desc: We'll visit three great cities in the shadow of Venice: Padova (Padua), with its university life and famed basilica; Verona and its Roman ruins; and Ravenna, for its shimmering mosaics.

programme.title: Disney Cruise Line
programme.desc: When Disney launched its first ship in 1998, The Disney Magic, it was unlike any other. Painted black to mimic classic ships from the age of cruising, the ship was decked out like only Disney could muster. Disney then bought an island in the Bahamas to serve as a destination for cruise guests only.

programme.title: The Old World Connection
programme.desc: A long, mountainous passage connects North and South America. Here, hundreds of thousands of species live in one of the richest and most diverse places on earth the Caribbean rainforests.

programme.title: New Releases
programme.desc: Check out some of our new content!

programme.title: S8E10 - The Netherlands: Beyond Amsterdam
programme.desc: Zipping from Haarlem to Rotterdam, and from Delft to the former Zuiderzee, we'll enjoy fragrant cheese markets, soggy polderland, charming towns, and windmills both new and old.

programme.title: Hobart Tasmaina
programme.desc: In Tasmania, Jason immerses himself into the natural world by visiting Cradle Mountain and Weindorfer’s Forest Walk. He also experiences Hobart's cafe culture, and goes on the hunt for fresh seafood.

programme.title: A Desert Feast
programme.desc: Morocco (Sahara): Tony traverses the Moroccan desert with one goal in mind, to eat a mud-oven-roasted sheep.

programme.title: Key West
programme.desc: We are on island time for this episode. Learn about the Key's treasure hunting history at the Mel Fisher Museum. Explore Fort Jefferson, an isolated fort in the Gulf of Mexico that defended the islands. American literature enthusiasts will enjoy a look at Ernest Hemingway's Key West home.

programme.title: S7E3 - Rome: Back-Street Riches
programme.desc: We explore Rome on a more intimate scale — dodging Vespas in Trastevere, roaming through the historic Jewish Ghetto, and enjoying art treasures in a string of rarely visited churches to uncover the charms of hidden Rome.

programme.title: Village of Swimming Cows
programme.desc: What happens when eco-minded, city-dwelling Berliners move in with Polish farmers in the country? Take a charming, extraordinarily funny look at how friendship and communication can overcome boundaries, and how nourishing the mind, body, and spirit begins with love and respect for Mother Earth.

programme.title: Naples and the Amalfi Coast
programme.desc: Deep in the heart of Naples, Italy is the ideal launching point for exploring Italy's great historic treasures. Marvel at the ancient city of Pompeii, and the eerily captured devastation of Mount Vesuvius. Hop a ferry to the isle of Capri and drive the spectacular Amalfi Coast.

programme.title: Rome
programme.desc: Rudy is in the city where all roads lead - Roma. We begin in ancient Rome - the Forum, Palatine Hill, Colosseum, and the Baths of Caracalla. Then, we explore the modern city of Rome with its ambient life in the streets, cafes, pizzerias and gelaterias.

programme.title: S7E9 - North England's Lake District and Durham
programme.desc: Hiking through the Cumbrian Lake District, we'll admire idyllic lakes, discover misty waterfalls, tour a slate mine, and climb up to a stony summit. Then we’ll play some cricket, hike Hadrian’s Wall, and be dazzled by Durham’s cathedral.

programme.title: Cod Crazy
programme.desc: Portugal: Portuguese cuisine holds a dear place in Tony's culinary heart. Tony travels to Porto, home of the famous Port wine, where he is immediately exposed to the codfish and the almost mythical place it holds in Portuguese cuisine and culture.

programme.title: San Sebastian: A Food Lover's Town
programme.desc: San Sebastian, Spain: Tony explores the food-crazed Basque culture. Tony's guide, Chef Luis Irizar, takes Tony into the underworld of Basque gastronomic societies. Later, Tony explores the city's tapas bars.

programme.title: Childhood Flavors
programme.desc: Arcachon, France: Here, Bourdain first learned to love food as a child. Returning for a trip down memory lane, Tony enjoys childhood staples, including steak frites, gaufres (waffles), soupe de pecheur (fisherman's soup) and fresh oysters.

programme.title: Stuffed like a Pig
programme.desc: Portugal & Southwest France: Visiting his boss's family farm, Tony helps slaughter and feast on a pig the family has been fattening all year. Then, Tony heads to France to experience the rich delights of a foie gras farm.

programme.title: A Desert Feast
programme.desc: Morocco (Sahara): Tony traverses the Moroccan desert with one goal in mind, to eat a mud-oven-roasted sheep.

programme.title: Italy: Part 2
programme.desc: The brilliance and grandeur of Italy is demonstrated in five captivating settings. Feel like a tall wildflower in the sun and breeze as the hills of Altomonte billow off into the distance, sooth every aching nerve as you absorb the perfect view along the Tiber River, and more.

programme.title: Shedd Aquarium: Wild Reef
programme.desc: Experience the wonder of the Shedd Aquarium’s wild reef as light dances off the colorful aquatic sea life that peacefully swim past in the crystal-clear water. Ambient sound makes you feel as if you are deep beneath the ocean.

programme.title: Thailand, The Andaman Islands
programme.desc: Andaman Coast towns such as Phuket are well known to backpackers and sun seekers. Join Rudy as he paddles through hidden entrances of small islands to find mangroves few people ever see. Also, visit the dramatic limestone cliffs and rock formations jutting out from translucent waters of Phang-nga Bay.

programme.title: Estonia
programme.desc: Venture to Estonia and the islands of Saaremaa and Muhu where you will find windmills, thatch-roofed farmhouses, and quiet waters. Rudy interviews Mart Laar who took over Estonia under tough conditions following the withdrawal of Soviet troops and turned it into a dynamic country.

programme.title: St. Petersburg, Russia
programme.desc: From the splendors of Peterhof to the quiet grace of the city's canals, this former capital built by a czar has reclaimed its position as one of the world's great destinations. St. Petersburg--enjoying a renaissance since its favorite son, Vladimir Putin, ascended to office—has lifted its gloom.

programme.title: Buenos Aires, Argentina
programme.desc: The style and verve of one of South America's most beautiful capitals is highlighted with Argentina's national dance, the tango, as well as the energy that its diverse population brings to the urban landscape. Discover a very special place in Buenos Aires.

programme.title: Mendoza, Argentina
programme.desc: As Rudy ascends into the thin air of the Andes, he stops to visit the graveyard of those who died climbing Aconcagua. Rudy’s next choice for high-altitude adventure? Getting soaked whitewater rafting. Back at sea level he meets winemakers whose elegant Malbecs are shaking up the world's wine market.

programme.title: India: From Girl to Woman
programme.desc: “First marriage and then love.” This Indian proverb describes Indian society quite accurately in terms of how the tradition of marriage is perceived and experienced in the country. In India, people do not just marry whoever they wish. It is the family that decides in an arrangement called Shaadi.

programme.title: From Peru to Tanzania
programme.desc: There are places on Earth worthy of absolute preservation and protection for all future generations. Meet people from Puerto Rico, Maryland, Peru, Tanzania, Slovakia, and Cambodia who all share an abiding belief in a sacred, healthy Earth.

programme.title: Sea Change
programme.desc: Fresh water is one of Earth’s sacred resources. Lake Turkana’s freshwater resources are vital to countless people who rely on it for sustenance. When a dam threatened to disturb the Lake’s ecosystem, some took action to protect their home.

programme.title: Portugal's Via Publicae
programme.desc: Open your ears to those who call this land home, and who will unveil its unique characteristics to you. Via Publicae was once an ancient Roman road and trade route that stretched from Braga in the north to Lisbon in the south of Portugal. Roman influence was once very strong in this region.

programme.title: The Route of the Two Oceans
programme.desc: The thin ridge that links the two Americas is a miniature world unto itself and concentrates a vast amount of diversity into a small area of land. Follow the Inter-American Highway from Panama City to the Isthmus of Rivas in Nicaragua, the narrowest ridge of Central America.

programme.title: Eating on the Edge of Nowhere
programme.desc: Cambodia and Japan: Taking his obsession with the film Apocalypse Now a little too seriously, Tony sets out for Pailin, reputed to be one of the most dangerous towns on earth. After his journey, Tony returns to Japan.

programme.title: The Cook Who Came in From the Cold
programme.desc: St. Petersburg, Russia: Tony plays spy in Russia and sets off to locate the best blinis and borscht St. Petersburg has to offer.

programme.title: S7E9 - North England's Lake District and Durham
programme.desc: Hiking through the Cumbrian Lake District, we'll admire idyllic lakes, discover misty waterfalls, tour a slate mine, and climb up to a stony summit. Then we’ll play some cricket, hike Hadrian’s Wall, and be dazzled by Durham’s cathedral.

programme.title: S8E9 - Amsterdam
programme.desc: Uniquely entertaining Amsterdam shows off its Rembrandts and Van Goghs, rivers of bikes, and pot-filled coffeeshops — all under gabled facades leaning out over placid canals.

programme.title: Disney Animal Kingdom
programme.desc: Explore the process of designing and creating Disney’s Animal Kingdom with incredible behind-the-scenes footage. Discover how Disney incorporates live animals into their attractions and uncover the time taken to create authentic habitats that allow visitors to experience a safari or jungle trek.

programme.title: Forests Between Two Worlds
programme.desc: At the edge of the Old World there is a peninsula connecting Europe and Africa. With warm sheltering tropics in its southern regions and a mountainous north of wet and old forests, the Iberian Peninsula contains mystery and diversity.

programme.title: New Releases
programme.desc: Check out some of our new content!

programme.title: S8E9 - Amsterdam
programme.desc: Uniquely entertaining Amsterdam shows off its Rembrandts and Van Goghs, rivers of bikes, and pot-filled coffeeshops — all under gabled facades leaning out over placid canals.

programme.title: Perth Western Australia
programme.desc: In Western Australia, Jason visits vineyards, goes on a food adventure for crayfishes, truffles, and finger limes, and visits a Brazilian food in Perth city.

programme.title: Traditional Tastes
programme.desc: Morocco (Cities): Tony is invited to experience the culinary heart and distinct walled medinas (districts) of the Moroccan city Fes.

programme.title: Savannah
programme.desc: We visit the old South and enjoy some sweet tea in Savannah. On this episode, we will stroll the city’s beautiful squares, as well as visit its civil war past at Old Fort Jackson. Then, we head up the stairs of the famous Tybee Island lighthouse and visit the Savannah Railroad museum.

programme.title: S7E4 - Florence: Heart of the Renaissance
programme.desc: In Florence, we'll revel in the genius of Michelangelo and Botticelli, climb the dome that kicked off the Renaissance, and cross the Arno to take in modern-day artisan life.

programme.title: Running of the Bulls
programme.desc: The Festival of San Fermin in Pamplona, Spain is a deeply rooted celebration of traditional and folkloric events, including the Running of the Bulls. Experience the incredible energy each morning for eight consecutive days as thousands of people run ahead of six, 2,000-pound charging bulls.

programme.title: The Cook Who Came in From the Cold
programme.desc: St. Petersburg, Russia: Tony plays spy in Russia and sets off to locate the best blinis and borscht St. Petersburg has to offer.

programme.title: So Much Vodka, So Little Time
programme.desc: St. Petersburg, Russia: Tony continues his mission with a tour of local working-class specialties. He tries his hand at ice-fishing, drinks a lot of vodka, feasts on Russian foods, eats smoked fish and ends the outing with a dip in the outdoor cold pool.

programme.title: Edinburgh and Scotland
programme.desc: Friendly and feisty, Scotland makes us feel right at home. In Edinburgh, we climb the ramparts of this city's famous castle, shop for kilts, visit mysterious Rosslyn Chapel and gasp on a ghost tour. Then we head to historic St. Andrew's to practice our swing on the world's most famous golf course.

programme.title: Barcelona and Costa Brava
programme.desc: A Mediterranean marvel, Barcelona simmers with beautiful beaches, medieval mazes, eye popping art and hypnotic architecture. From tapas bars, to surrealist art, to Modernist structures, we will feast on Barcelona's delights.

programme.title: S7E10 - Venice: City of Dreams
programme.desc: In Venice, we'll sample the splendor of the Doge's Palace, St. Mark's Basilica, Grand Canal, and masterpieces from the Venetian Renaissance — then take a glide on a gondola.

programme.title: Stoked on Fishing - An Unforgettable Trip, South Lake, Part Two
programme.desc: This show was filmed in late October of 2019. Four months prior, in June of 2019, Tim Carnahan was diagnosed with Glioblastoma, Brain Cancer. According to Tim's medical team, his life expectancy could be between three months and 18 months. Fast forward to now, 2020; today's update is one we hoped would never come. With a heavy heart and tear-filled eyes, we share with you that Tim Carnahan has passed away after battling for close to 12 months. It only fits that the last words to pass his lips were I love you, Lory, and keep fishing. While his time on earth was cut short, the amount of joy he experienced and shared with others was genuinely tremendous and will never be forgotten. If you would like to help out in any way, lory and friends have put together a Go Fund Me page to ease the financial burden of medical bills and afford lory some time to greave and transition into life without Tim. We love you, Tim. Rest in peace, buddy.

programme.title: Stoked on Fishing - The Magdalena Bay Experience, Part Two
programme.desc: One of the best parts of traveling is the pleasant surprises that come along every trip. In last week's episode, Shea McIntee and the crew had a remarkable day of Marlin fishing in Madalena Bay. programme.title: Stoked on Fishing - An Unforgettable Trip, South Lake, Part Two
programme.desc: This show was filmed in late October of 2019. Four months prior, in June of 2019, Tim Carnahan was diagnosed with Glioblastoma, Brain Cancer. According to Tim's medical team, his life expectancy could be between three months and 18 months. Fast forward to now, 2020; today's update is one we hoped would never come. With a heavy heart and tear-filled eyes, we share with you that Tim Carnahan has passed away after battling for close to 12 months. It only fits that the last words to pass his lips were I love you, Lory, and keep fishing. While his time on earth was cut short, the amount of joy he experienced and shared with others was genuinely tremendous and will never be forgotten. If you would like to help out in any way, lory and friends have put together a Go Fund Me page to ease the financial burden of medical bills and afford lory some time to greave and transition into life without Tim. We love you, Tim. Rest in peace, buddy.

programme.title: Expect The Unexpected
programme.desc: PBR Bullrider Dustin Elliott hunts elk in Colorado, while Team Elk host Brandon Bates manages an unexpected situation in Wyoming.

programme.title: The Rut is On
programme.desc: Cameron Hanes stalks a giant bull in New Mexico, while Mark Garcia of Archer Xtreme gets in the middle of rutting bulls in Colorado.

programme.title: Kansas Whitetail
programme.desc: Last year Larry Weishuhn took a gorgeous 171-inch 10-point whitetail in Kansas. Now he returns to the sunflower state to hunt with Stan Christensen of Kansas Trophy Whitetails once again to see if they can recreate the same magic during muzzleloader season.

programme.title: Yellow Creek Wyoming
programme.desc: Wind and cold weather are on the docket for hunters in Wyoming with Dallas Safari Club’s Outfitter of the Year B. Joe Coy. Getting into range of these mature whitetails is tough when the stiff wind keeps changing directions on Mr. Whitetail.

programme.title: High Altitude Elk & Low Light Hogs
programme.desc: Chris Dorsey takes in two of North America's thrilling hunts with a elk hunt in western Colorado and a nighttime hog hunt in North Texas.

programme.title: Risks and Trepidations
programme.desc: Fourteen days into their race, with their energy reserves drained and food rations diminished, the brigade is on a mission to find new ways of conserving energy, supplementing their diet, and keeping morale up. Their whitewater skills are put to the test as they navigate a series of intense downstream rapids in their 29 foot 2500 lbs voyageur canoe, following the ebbs and flows of the Hayes River, as it twists and turns across the northeastern stretches of Manitoba. Faced with a dilemma to go fast or err on the side of caution, the group is divided and tensions come to a head, but it’s Wanda that suffers the biggest blow.

programme.title: A Traditional Catfish and Turtle Hunt
programme.desc: Jim heads down south to do a little traditional catfish and turtle hunting with some of the best of the best.

programme.title: Broadway Bucks Part 2
programme.desc: As rifle season continues, Tom goes the extra mile to ensure a one hundred percent success rate.

programme.title: The Spoils of Decoying Whitetails
programme.desc: Longtime Bowhunter Magazine Contributor Danny Farris decoys rutting Illinois bucks at eye level.

programme.title: Panhandlin' for a Buck!
programme.desc: Gordon Whittington is headed to the Panhandle of Texas to hunt with T-Fork Outfitters, Dr. Kroll talks warm season food plots, Laden Force discusses Sig's new BDX system and Jeremy Moore kicks off a three part series on shed dogs.

programme.title: Old-School Deer Hunt, Part 1
programme.desc: Mike and friends hunt deer and hogs at Gopher Plantation, a replica of a South Georgia farm as existed at the turn of the 19th century.

programme.title: Trout Help
programme.desc: Chef Scott Leysath is home in his kitchen for this one, and he’s got a bunch of Trout to cook. Today’s guests feature Susie Jimenez, Tommy Gomes, Stacy Lyn Harris, Brad Fenson, Cee Dub, and Buddy T.

programme.title: The Reluctant Bull Rider
programme.desc: Derek joins Hall-of-Famer Gary Leffew at his first-class bull riding school.

programme.title: New Smyrna Beach Redfish
programme.desc: Show host, Jason South joins Capt. Mike Rathjen for some incredible redfish action in the Ponce Inlet. They find monster redfish schooled up and biting great.

programme.title: Offshore Gulf Grouper
programme.desc: Show host, Jason South joins Capt. Seth Hayes for some incredible offshore gag grouper action off the coast of Ft.Myers.

programme.title: Bad Mood
programme.desc: Bou and Rob fish clients in the Cheeca Lodge & Spa Tarpon Invitational. They battle through wind and rain in this, the first tournament of the tarpon season.

programme.title: Golden Fly Part 2
programme.desc: It’s Day 2 of the Golden Fly Tarpon Tournament in Islamorada, FL. Rob is fishing tournament champion Andy Mill and Bou is fishing his friend Paul Nute.

programme.title: Beautiful Danger
programme.desc: Epic adventure awaits at the Dry Tortugas, but fishing off the grid is no easy task. As the SFTV crew discovers, preparation is everything.

programme.title: Young Salt, Old Spirit
programme.desc: Armed with the skills of generations past, rough and tumble New Englanders teach the SFTV crew how to catch the region's sporty summertime species.

programme.title: Atlantic Gladiators
programme.desc: New England pelagics like swordfish and bluefin tuna bring more than sport. It's a heavyweight, high octane battle, and the angler is the underdog.

programme.title: Beachfront
programme.desc: Tarpon are caught right out in front of Panama City Beach condos. Justin and a friend give visitors a front row seat to the silver king’s spectacular aerial dance.

programme.title: Jacks Be Roiling
programme.desc: When word gets out that Jack Crevalle are in a feeding frenzy, Justin and fellow Captain Kyle Pitts speed down the Intracoastal Waterway to find them doing just that.

programme.title: Hot and Hevi
programme.desc: It’s the Wisconsin Waterfowl Opener & Pickett dominates an upland hunt in the afternoon.

programme.title: Flint Oak Upland
programme.desc: Join Jeff Fuller, along with his sons, Clayton and Callahan, and the dogs of Soggy Acres Retrievers as they travel to Flint Oak Hunting Resort in Kansas for an upland hunt to remember.

programme.title: The Harvest You Reap
programme.desc: Ron and Betsy Spomer have purchased their forever-home - a spectacular ranch in Idaho - and this is Ron's first season hunting his new honey hole.

programme.title: Get Their Good Tidings
programme.desc: Chris Dorsey returns to the mountains of Colorado to hunt mule deer in the rut.

programme.title: Moritz Simon Geist and the sounds of Polestar 2
programme.desc: Polestar has teamed up with qualified robotics engineer and musician Moritz Simon Geist to create a whole new type of music. Moritz has made a name for himself by building robots that create music from unlikely sources. Now, one such source is Polestar 2.

programme.title: Roborace - Our first music EP is out!
programme.desc: Initially, project Roborace is the extreme competition of full-size electric racing cars driven by artificial intelligence. The cars were designed by Daniel Simon, who previously worked on vehicles for movies such as "Tron: Legacy", "Oblivion", sequels of "Star Wars" and others. Introducing the coming "Season Beta" of the robot competition, this futuristic project evolves with starting its own original music band in collaboration with several contemporary musicians from various countries to create their first EP "Beta". The work was made together with Russian synth-music artist Vlad Green (aka TæT Music) and Belgian progressive drummer Benjamin Baert. More releases to come soon.

programme.title: Audi TechTalk: Carbon Neutrality
programme.desc: By 2025, all Audi production sites are planned to have a carbon-neutral manufacturing footprint. Audi will address upstream production processes together with its suppliers in order to identify CO2 reduction potential here as well and to make the manufacturing stage of its products as climate-friendly as possible. programme.title: Animation: Audi RS e-tron GT – Electric Quattro and Recuperation
programme.desc: The e-tron GT quattro and the RS e-tron GT usually drive with electric all-wheel drive, only the “efficiency” mode of the Audi drive select dynamic handling system prioritizing the front-wheel drive. In event of a slippery road surface, high power requirements, or fast cornering, the electric motor for rear-wheel drive is also activated here, and around five times faster than with a mechanical quattro drivetrain. The electric all-wheel drive regulates the drive torque distribution between the axles – continuously, fully variably, and within a few thousandths of a second. The quattro principle of the four-wheel drive that Audi introduced to the market more than 40 years ago presents itself on a new, fascinating technological level. When the driver releases the right-hand pedal, the drive usually switches to sailing, allowing the gran turismo to glide with elegance and efficiency. By contrast, the car recuperates in overrun mode in the “dynamic” mode of Audi drive select. - Audi RS e-tron GT: Combined electric power consumption in kWh/100 km (62.1 mi)*: 20.2–19.3 (NEDC), 22.5–20.6 (WLTP); combined CO2 emissions in g/km (g/mi)*: 0 - Information on fuel consumption and CO2 emissions as well as efficiency classes in ranges depending on the tires and alloy wheel rims used.

programme.title: Audi Annual Press Conference 2020
programme.desc: 2020 was dominated by a global pandemic and great upheaval, which therefore shifted the focus even more strongly to the question of responsible actions. As part of the automotive industry, we are responsible for our employees and customers, for stable economic growth, and for a sustainable business model. Despite – or precisely because of – the current challenges, we are in a position where we can make a big difference. At Audi, we see ambitious climate targets, the paradigm shift toward software, and the impetus created by new competitors as an opportunity to play an active part in shaping the future of mobility. Our Board of Management team, which has been active in a new constellation for about a year, will provide an overview on how Audi handled the unusual year of 2020 and on which future topics we have our sights firmly set.
